@node Release @value{PACKAGE}-@value{VERSION}
@unnumberedsubsec Major changes for release @value{PACKAGE}-@value{VERSION}
@cindex release @value{PACKAGE}-@value{VERSION}

@quotation
@b{Note Well:} This release has never been publicly released.  This subpackage is no longer
maintained by the OpenSS7 Project.
@end quotation

This is the fourth @cite{OpenSS7 Project} release of the @cite{@value{PACKAGE_TITLE}} package.  The
package provides @manref{dlgn(4)}, @manref{mercd(4)} and @manref{pmacd(4)} device drivers, as well
as @manref{dvbm(4)} and @manref{sctmr(4)} modules.  Additional drivers are the @manref{gncfd(4)} and
@manref{gpio(4)} modules.  The package contains all the necessary manual pages and other
documentation for components in an OpenSS7-style @manref{autoconf(1)} tarball.

THis release is the fourth public release.  The release includes maintenance suport for recent
distributions, production kernels and tool chain, but also includes feature upgrades and bug fixes.
It deprecates previous releases: please upgrade before reporting bugs on previous releases.

Major features since the last public release are:

@itemize -
@item
Documentation license upgraded to GFDL 1.3.

@item
Updated tool chain to @file{m4-1.4.13}, @file{automake-1.10.2}, @file{bison-2.4.1},
@file{libtool-2.2.6a}, @file{texinfo-4.13a}.

@end itemize

@emph{This is a public alpha release of the package: it deprecates previous
releases.  Please see @file{README-alpha} in the release, or @refman{Maturity}.}

This is a public alpha release of the package.  This package is complete but untested.  It is being
released for testing by the community.  If you are interested in testing of this package, contact
@email{info@@openss7.com}.

As with other OpenSS7 releases, this release configures, compiles, installs and builds RPMs and DEBs
for a wide range of Linux 2.4 and 2.6 @manref{rpm(8)} and @manref{dpkg(1)} based distributions, and
can be used on production kernels without patching or recompiling the kernel.

This package is publicly released strictly under the @cite{GNU Affero General Public License Version
3}; however, commercial licensing is available.  The release is available as an @manref{autoconf(1)}
tarball, SRPM, DSC, and a set of binary RPMs and DEBs for popular distributions.  See the
@uref{http://www.openss.org/@value{PACKAGE}_pkg.html,package page} for the @mantype{autoconf(1)}
tarballs, SRPMs, DSCs and binary RPMs and DEBs.  See the
@uref{http://www.openss7.org/repos.html,repository page} for information concerning network
installation and update sources.

See @uref{http://www.openss7.org/codefiles/@value{PACKAGE}-@value{VERSION}/ChangeLog,ChangeLog} and
@uref{http://www.openss7.org/codefiles/@value{PACKAGE}-@value{VERSION}/NEWS,NEWS} in the release for
more information.  Also, see the @file{@value{PACKAGE}.pdf} manual in the release (also in
@uref{http://www.openss7.org/@value{PACKAGE}_manual.html,html}).

For the news release, see @uref{http://www.openss7.org/rel20081029_M.html}.

